item.title: Virtualbox leaving whonix logs , is it safe?
item.dc:creator: Patrick
item.description:
Because you’re “not really” supposed to run Tails in a VM to being with. Tails warns against using VMs. (https://tails.boum.org/doc/advanced_topics/virtualization/index.de.html)

Tails is only amnesic if you use it from live media.

There is no feature for a VM to reconfigure the host to not create logs.
